The Hawks launched an anti-crime campaign at the V&amp;A Waterfront in Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - The Hawks launched an anti-crime campaign at the V&amp;A Waterfront in Cape Town on Saturday ahead of the festive season.The Card Crime Awareness campaign will take place over the next couple of weekends to educate consumers about safety tips, to avoid being victims of card fraud over the festive season.Earlier this week, the South African Banking Risk Information Centre (Sabric) and South African Police Service (SAPS) launched the Safer Banking campaign, in a bid to tackle the increase in crime that usually takes place during this period.Sabric says banks have lost more than R509 million due to card fraud.The Hawks' Lieutenant Colonel Jerome Hardenberg says there will be an increase in police visibility in and around malls over the next couple of weeks. We will be doing this over four Saturdays and we re kicking it off in the Waterfront, mixed with local people and tourists to heighten awareness around card fraud. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)